<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am not sure I have ever read a better encaps=
ulation of what it means to be a startup founder. You throw out a wildly am=
bitious vision of the future in your pitch meetings, and then you go back t=
o the office and google around to see if it=E2=80=99s possible. You just ca=
n=E2=80=99t do that with a public company, is the problem.</p>
